Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and dice @Carrot{3%ounce} into small pieces. Halve, peel, and finely
chop @Yellow Onion{1}. Dice @Tomato{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @Italian Chicken Sausage Mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into
pieces, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

Add another drizzle of olive oil to pot with sausage, then stir in carrot,
onion, and a big @Salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are
just softened and sausage is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add tomato, half the @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (use the rest as you
like), and ¼ tsp @Garlic Powder{1/4%tsp} to pot. (You'll use more garlic
powder in the next step.) Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2} and 3 1/2 cups warm water, scraping up
any browned bits from bottom of pot.

Add half the @Farfalle{6%ounce} (all for 4). Cover and bring to a boil, then
immediately reduce heat to low. Simmer until pasta is al dente, ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; 
microwave until just softened, ~{10%seconds} (do not melt).

Stir in 1 TBSP @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}, ¼ tsp garlic powder, a pinch
of salt, and @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Halve @Ciabatta Bread{1} and toast until golden. Spread butter mixture onto
cut sides, then halve on a diagonal.

Stir @Baby Spinach{5%ounce} into pot with soup until wilted. Season with
plenty of salt and pepper.

Divide soup between bowls; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and a pinch of
chili flakes if desired. Serve with toasts on the side for dipping.